name: Canada: A Short History of Here
description: This course is intended for non-History students; History students are advised to take HIS263Y1 instead. Make sense of politics today and develop a deeper understanding of Canadian society and its institutions through the major events and demographic trends that have shaped the development of this country, while enhancing critical reading and thinking skills through short writing assignments. No research essay. *This course will not count towards History program requirements or as a pre-requisite for upper level courses.*
